text: Eschatotypa derogatella is a species of moth in the family Tineidae. It was described by Francis Walker in 1863. This species is endemic to New Zealand. ==References== ==External links== *Image of type specimen of Eschatotypa derogatella Category:Moths described in 1863 Category:Tineidae Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Endemic fauna of New Zealand Category:Taxa named by Francis Walker
